# Next.js Resume Website Project Setup

This guide will help you set up the Next.js project structure for your resume website and deploy it to Vercel.

## Step 1: Create a new Next.js project

```bash
npx create-next-app@latest resume-website
cd resume-website
```

## Step 2: Install required dependencies

```bash
npm install framer-motion react-intersection-observer @fortawesome/react-fontawesome @fortawesome/free-solid-svg-icons @fortawesome/free-brands-svg-icons
```

## Step 3: Project Structure

Create the following file structure:

```
resume-website/
├── public/
│   └── images/
├── src/
│   ├── components/
│   │   ├── Header.js
│   │   ├── Hero.js
│   │   ├── Education.js
│   │   ├── Experience.js
│   │   ├── Skills.js
│   │   ├── Publications.js
│   │   ├── Additional.js
│   │   ├── Contact.js
│   │   ├── Footer.js
│   │   ├── FlyingPlane.js
│   │   └── FoodAnimation.js
│   ├── styles/
│   │   ├── globals.css
│   │   └── Home.module.css
│   └── pages/
│       ├── index.js
│       └── _app.js
```

